source("theme_mine.R")
source("functions.R")

# load library
library(tidyverse)
library(ggthemes)
library(scales)
library(vegan)
library(ggrepel)
library(ggrastr)
library(countrycode)
library(ggrepel)

tidy_col <- c("#18BC9C","#CCBE93","#a6cee3","#1f78b4","#b2df8a","#fb9a99","#fdbf6f","#ff7f00","#cab2d6","#6a3d9a")
dj_2 <- dj %>% paste0(., "55")

Read result files

files <- list.files("out/disease_each/", pattern = "res.rmp.rds") %>% paste0("out/disease_each/", .)

i <- files[1]
df <- c()
for(i in files){
  temp <- read_rds(i)
  df <- rbind(df, temp)
}
df$name <- df$name %>% str_replace("species incertae sedis", "sp.")

r_max <- max(df$rel_disease, df$rel_load)
df$col <- ifelse(df$fdr > 0.1, "ns", ifelse(df$e > 0, "enriched", "depleted"))

Plot fold change of FDR

df2 <- df %>% filter(fdr < 0.05)
df2$ratio <- (abs(df2$e_adj) / abs(df2$e))

df.temp <- df2 %>% select(name, ratio, disease) %>% group_by(disease) %>% 
  summarise(e = DescTools::Gmean(ratio), error = DescTools::Gmean(ratio, conf.level = 0.95)[3], n = n()) %>% data.frame()
## Registered S3 method overwritten by 'DescTools':
##   method        from       
##   print.palette wesanderson
df.temp$error <- df.temp$error - df.temp$e
df.temp <- df.temp %>% arrange(e)

fac.lev <- df.temp$disease

p.effect <- ggplot(df.temp, aes(y = reorder(disease, e, mean), x = e)) +
  theme_mine() +  
  ggforestplot::geom_stripes(odd = "#80808010", even = "#00000000") +
  theme(panel.grid.major.y = element_line(colour = "gray80", size = 0.2)) +
  
  xlab("Fold change in effect sizes") +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
  
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1, vjust = 0.5)) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(xmax = e + error, xmin = e - error), width = 0) +  
  geom_point(col = dj[5]) +

  geom_vline(xintercept = 1, linetype = 2, col = "red") +
  coord_flip()
p.effect

Plot FDR with and without adjustment

temp1 <- df2 %>% select(name, fdr, disease) %>% mutate(data = "Before")
temp2 <- df2 %>% select(name, fdr = fdr_adj, disease) %>% mutate(data = "After")
df3 <- rbind(temp1, temp2)
df3$data <- factor(df3$data, levels = c("Before", "After"))
df3$disease <- df3$disease %>% factor(levels = fac.lev)

df3$fdr[df3$fdr < 1E-20] <- 1E-20

p.pval <- ggplot(df3, aes(y = disease, x = -log10(fdr), fill = data)) +
  theme_mine() +
  ggforestplot::geom_stripes(odd = "#80808010", even = "#00000000") +
  theme(panel.grid.major.y = element_line(colour = "gray80", size = 0.2)) +
  theme(axis.ticks.x = element_blank()) +
  theme(plot.margin = unit(c(0.5, 0.5, 0.1, 0.5), "lines")) +
  xlab("-log10(FDR)") +

  geom_boxplot(outlier.size = 0.1, outlier.color = "gray") +

  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1, vjust = 0.5)) + 
  geom_vline(xintercept = -log10(0.05), linetype = 2, col = "red") +
  scale_fill_manual(labels = c("Before adjustment", "After adjustment"), name = "", values = c(dj_2[5], dj[5])) +
  scale_color_manual(labels = c("Before adjustment", "After adjustment"), name = "", values = c(dj_2[5], dj[5])) + 
  theme(legend.position = "bottom") +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
  coord_flip()
p.pval

Plot FDR of Shannon diversity

temp <- df %>% filter(name == "Shannon diversity") %>% select(disease, p, p_adj) %>% gather("key", "value", -disease)
temp$value <- temp$value %>% p.adjust(method = "fdr")

keep <- temp$disease %in% fac.lev
temp <- temp[keep, ]
temp$disease <- factor(temp$disease, levels = fac.lev)

temp$value[temp$disease == "Crohn's disease"][1] <- 1E-20
temp$key <- factor(temp$key, levels = c("p", "p_adj"))


p.shannon <- ggplot(temp, aes(y = disease, x = -log10(value))) +
  theme_mine() +
  ggforestplot::geom_stripes(odd = "#80808010", even = "#00000000") +
  theme(panel.grid.major.y = element_line(colour = "gray80", size = 0.2)) +
  
  xlab("-log10(FDR)") +
  theme(panel.grid.minor = element_blank()) +

  geom_path(col = "black", arrow = arrow(length=unit(0.15,"cm"), type = "closed"), size = 0.2, aes(group = disease)) +
  geom_point(aes(col = key)) +    
  
  geom_vline(xintercept = -log10(0.05), linetype = 2, col = "red") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1, vjust = 0.5)) +

  scale_color_manual(labels = c("Before adjustment", "After adjustment"), name = "", values = c(dj_2[5], dj[5])) +  
  theme(legend.title = element_blank(), axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10)) +
  coord_flip()
p.shannon

Plot the number of significant species (FDR < 0.05)

threshold <- 0.05
temp1 <- df %>% filter(fdr < threshold) %>% group_by(disease) %>% summarise(n = n()) %>% data.frame()
temp1$method <- "Before adjustment"
temp2 <- df %>% filter(fdr_adj < threshold) %>% group_by(disease) %>% summarise(n = n()) %>% data.frame()
temp2$method <- "After adjustment"

temp <- rbind(temp1, temp2)
temp$method <- factor(temp$method, levels = c("Before adjustment", "After adjustment"))
temp$disease <- temp$disease %>% factor(levels = fac.lev)

p.bar <- ggplot(temp, aes(y = disease, x = n, fill = method)) +
  theme_mine() +
  ggforestplot::geom_stripes(odd = "#80808010", even = "#00000000") +
  theme(panel.grid.major.y = element_line(colour = "gray80", size = 0.2)) +
  theme(axis.ticks.x = element_blank()) +
  theme(plot.margin = unit(c(0.5, 0.5, 0.1, 0.5), "lines")) +
  
  xlab("Number of significance") +
  theme(panel.grid.minor = element_blank()) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1, vjust = 0.5)) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c(dj_2[5], dj[5])) +  
  
  scale_y_discrete(drop = FALSE) +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom", legend.title = element_blank()) +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", width = 0.8, position = position_dodge(width = 0.8)) +
  coord_flip()
p.bar

Plot species that lost significant associations

df2 <- df %>% filter(fdr < 0.05 & fdr_adj > 0.05)
df.temp <- df2$name %>% table() %>% data.frame() %>% arrange(-Freq)
colnames(df.temp) <- c("sp", "freq")

p.disapear <- df.temp %>% filter(freq > 4) %>% ggplot(aes(x = freq, y = reorder(sp, freq, sum))) +
  theme_mine() +
  theme(panel.grid.major.x = element_line(colour = "gray80", size = 0.2)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = dj[5], width = 0.6, alpha = 0.8) +
  
  theme(plot.margin=unit(c(0.5, 0.5, 10, 1), "lines")) +
  theme(axis.title.y = element_blank()) +
  xlab("No. of disease associations\nlost by adjustment")
p.disapear
